Definition.WordDefinition: Seventeen \Sev"en*teen`\, a. [OE. seventene, AS. seofont[=y]ne, i. e., seven-ten. Cf. {Seventy}.] One more than sixteen; ten and seven added; as, seventeen years. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
Seventeen \Sev"en*teen`\, n. 1. The number greater by one than sixteen; the sum of ten and seven; seventeen units or objects. [1913 Webster]
2. A symbol denoting seventeen units, as 17, or xvii. [1913 Webster]
seventeen adj : being one more than sixteen [syn: {17}, {xvii}] n : the cardinal number that is the sum of sixteen and one [syn: {17}, {XVII}]
